'''Austin Graham Bagnall''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|OBE|size=85%}} (30 November 1912 &ndash; 16 April 1986) was a New Zealand librarian, bibliographer and historian. He was born in [[Auckland]], New Zealand, on 30 November 1912.<ref name="DNZB Bagnall">{{DNZB|title=Austin Graham Bagnall|first= Penny|last= Griffith|id=5b1|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

In the [[1978 Birthday Honours|1978 Queen's Birthday Honours]], Bagnall was appointed an [[Order of the British Empire|Officer of the Order of the British Empire]] for services to New Zealand literature and the library profession.<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=47551 |date=3 June 1978 |page=6270 |supp=y }}</ref>

