'''Rajiv Smruthi Bhavan''' is a memorial and cultural center at [[Beach road, Visakhapatnam|Beach road]], [[Pandurangapuram, Visakhapatnam|Pandurangapuram]], [[Visakhapatnam]]. It was established in the year 2008 by the then Chief Minister of [[Andhra Pradesh]] [[Y. S. Rajasekhara Reddy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/current-affairs/280116/rajiv-bhavan-stands-as-hudhud-memorial.html|title=Visakhapatnam: Rajiv Bhavan stands as Hudhud Memorial|date=28 January 2016|newspaper=Deccan Chronicle|accessdate=29 September 2018}}</ref>
==About== This memorial and cultural center is dedicated to the former Prime Minister of India [[Rajiv Gandhi]]. This venue is permanent photo exhibition of Rajiv Gandhi <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/multiactivity-centre-mooted-at-rajiv-smruthi-bhavan/article6626986.ece|title=Multi-activity centre mooted at Rajiv Smruthi Bhavan|first=G. S.|last=Subrahmanyam|date=23 November 2014|publisher=|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref> and is also a center for classical and [[carnatic music]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Rajiv-Smruthi-Bhavan|title=Rajiv Smruthi Bhavan: Latest News, Videos and Photos - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>
